I have an Angular landing page. Below the hero section I have a stats 
row that currently shows static text on one line like:

  "13+ Systems   |   6 Phases   |   3 Human Perspectives   |   ..."

Replace this with a REFIRE-style scroll-triggered section where each 
stat animates in one by one as the user scrolls into view. No external 
libraries — Vanilla TypeScript + CSS only. IntersectionObserver drives 
everything.

---

### Layout — vertical stacked reveal, not horizontal row

Do NOT keep the stats on one line. Stack them vertically with generous 
spacing, full width. Each stat is its own visual moment:

  [large number animates up]
  [label fades in 200ms after number finishes]

  [next number — only appears after scroll brings it into view]
  [its label]

  ... and so on

Container: max-width 900px, centered, padding 8vw 6vw
Background: var(--color-bg-surface)  [#111620]
Each stat block: min-height 30vh, display flex, align-items center

